    "content_hash": "1c361dc11d6be924",
    "department": "Enterprise",
    "description": "Role Overview\n\nLocation: Netherlands (Zoetermeer office)\n\nReporting to: Sr. Distribution Account Manager, Enterprise Sales - EMEA\n\nRegion: Benelux \u0026 Nordics\n\nThe Distribution Account Manager is responsible for managing distributor relationships, driving regional business plans and growth initiatives, overseeing buying plans, and ensuring sales execution to meet sell-in and sell-through targets within the assigned region. This role requires strong collaboration with internal teams and distributors to optimize performance and support overall business objectives.\n\nThis role includes developing strong distributor partnerships, optimizing sell-in and sell-through performance, and building comprehensive business plans aligned with NETGEAR’s strategic goals. The DAM is accountable for forecasting, planning, and managing distributor inventory to maintain stock health and drive sustainable growth.\n\n\n\n\n\nKEY RESPONSIBILITIES\n\nDistributor Relationship Management\n\n - Serve as the primary point of contact for all distributors in the assigned region.\n\n - Build and maintain strong, trust-based relationships with key decision-makers at all levels.\n\n - Conduct regular business reviews to assess performance and define corrective actions.\n\n - Ensure distributors comply with NETGEAR policies, pricing structures, branding, and operational standards.\n\n - Advocate for distributor needs while ensuring alignment with NETGEAR strategy.\n\nRegional Business Growth \u0026 Strategy\n\n - Develop strategic business plans with NETGEAR Sales Leaders to support regional growth targets.\n\n - Analyse market trends, competitive activity, and sell-through performance to identify opportunities.\n\n - Collaborate with marketing and channel teams to execute localized campaigns and partner incentives.\n\n - Monitor sell-in and sell-through performance to ensure continuous improvement.\n\n - Use business intelligence and insights to capitalise on emerging opportunities.\n\nBuying Plan Ownership\n\n - Create, negotiate, and manage distributor buying plans aligned with quarterly and annual sell-in and sell-through targets.\n\n - Collaborate with distributors on forecasting, replenishment planning, and inventory management.\n\n - Optimize inventory levels to reduce overstock and prevent stock-outs.\n\n - Coordinate with PLM, Supply Chain, and Demand Planning for accurate forecasting and product availability.\n\n - Adjust buying strategies based on market insights, performance trends, and seasonality.\n\nSales Execution \u0026 Performance Management\n\n - Achieve regional sell-through target through strong operational and sales execution.\n\n - Conduct performance analysis and provide insights to improve distributor productivity.\n\n - Support product launches with training materials and execution planning.\n\n - Manage pricing, promotions, rebates, and channel programs to maintain competitiveness.\n\n - Maintain visibility into distributor pipeline activity and conversion metrics.\n\nCross-Functional Collaboration\n\n - Collaborate closely with Sales, Marketing, Finance, Product Management, PLM, Operations, and Supply Chain teams.\n\n - Maintain strong, proactive communication with Sales Leaders for alignment on strategic priorities.\n\n - Align on joint opportunities, customer engagements, and channel programs.\n\n - Provide market insights, forecasting data, and operational feedback to internal teams.\n\n - Deliver product and category feedback to influence roadmap and strategy.\n\nRequired Qualifications\n\n - Fluent in Dutch and English (C1 level or higher)\n\n - 5+ years of experience in distribution management or a similar channel-focused role.\n\n - Strong track record working with distribution and reseller partners.\n\n - Action-oriented with a strong drive for results.\n\n - Excellent communication, interpersonal, and presentation skills.\n\n - Strong cross-functional collaboration capabilities.\n\n - High proficiency with Excel, PowerPoint, and analytical tools.\n\n - Strong analytical and problem-solving abilities.\n\n - Adaptable and effective in a fast-paced environment.\n\n - Strong negotiation and account management abilities.\n\n - Ability to build productive internal and external relationships.\n\n - Experience in strategic planning, forecasting, and business execution.\n\nPreferred Qualifications\n\n - Technical understanding of networking solutions.\n\n - Knowledge of Switching, Wireless, and Pro AV.\n\n - Experience in Salesforce is highly desirable\n\n\n\n\nCompany Statement/Values:  \n\nAt NETGEAR, we are on a mission to unleash the full potential of connectivity with intelligent solutions that delight and protect. We turn ideas into innovative networking products that connect people, power businesses, and advance the way we live.  \n\nWe're a performance-driven, talented and connected team that's committed to delivering world-class products for our customers. As a company, we value our employees as the most essential building blocks of our success. And as teammates, we commit to taking our work to the Next Gear by living our values: we Dare to Transform the future, Connect and Delight our customers, Communicate Courageously with each other and collaborate to Win It Together. You’ll find our values woven through our processes, present in our decisions, and celebrated throughout our culture. \n\nWe strive to attract top talent and create a great workplace where people feel engaged, inspired, challenged, proud and respected. If you are creative, forward-thinking, passionate about technology and are looking for a rewarding career to make an impact, then you've got what it takes to succeed at NETGEAR. Join our network and help us shape the future of connectivity. \n\nNETGEAR hires based on merit. All qualified applicants will receive equal consideration for employment. All your information will be kept confidential according to EEO guidelines.",
    "employment_type": "FullTime",
